"ObtainFrogusStage1Answer0"                = "Hey buddy, I have noticed you barely touch your food, what is going on?";
"ObtainFrogusStage1Dialog0"                = "Yeah, you know what, I think I want some fish, could you catch me some? There is a lake nearby I think you can try there.";
"ObtainFrogusStage1Answer1"                = "All right, let us see what I can do. I think I will come up with something on next day.";
"ObtainFrogusStage3Answer0"                = "Oi mate, here is fish you have asked for. From very same lake you described.";
"ObtainFrogusStage3Dialog0"                = "Cheers mate, that is what I am talking about! Real fresh fish, el belissimo! Now I know this lake is good, think I will spend some time there by myself. Thanks again!";
"ObtainFrogusStage3Answer1"                = "No problem!";
"ObtainFrogusStage5Answer0"                = "Hey, what is that you are playing with?";
"ObtainFrogusStage5Dialog0"                = "Ah, found it on the lake. Round and rolling! Also smells like slime but it is okay. Here, take it, I am done playing with it.";
"ObtainFrogusStage5Answer1"                = "Thank you, I think I know what to do with it.";
"ObtainBoberStage2Answer0"                 = "Hey, do you know where all the eggs went?";
"ObtainBoberStage2Dialog0"                 = "Wow! I do not know anything about this, but I can look for it, ask me tomorrow, maybe I will find something.";
"ObtainBoberStage2Dialog1"                 = "I do not know anything and, honestly, I do not care.";
"ObtainBoberStage2Answer1"                 = "Thank you, I will come see you tomorrow!";
"ObtainBoberStage3Answer0"                 = "Well, did you find anything?";
"ObtainBoberStage3Dialog0"                 = "Nope, still looking.";
"ObtainBoberStage4Dialog0"                 = "Aha, I found all the eggs, well, you made me run! I suspect that they just rolled away or maybe the wind blew them away, I put them back in place, now they definitely will not roll away.";
"ObtainBoberStage6Answer0"                 = "The eggs are missing again, do you know anything about it?";
"ObtainBoberStage6Dialog0"                 = "What, again? Oh my! Okay, I will look again, but after I find it, you better come up with something so that this does not happen again.";
"ObtainBoberStage6Dialog1"                 = "Ahahahahahahahaha! Seriously? Well, screw them.";
"ObtainBoberStage8Dialog0"                 = "Here they are, finally. Listen, I do not want to run around looking for the missing eggs again if something else happens to them. Ask someone else, maybe they can help, we need to solve this problem somehow.";
"ObtainBoberStage8Answer0"                 = "Okay, I will ask around.";
"ObtainBoberStage9Answer0"                 = "Maybe you know what to do with these constantly rolling eggs?";
"ObtainBoberStage9Dialog0"                 = "Hmm, I do not know how to help you with this, but I think I know someone who knows what to do. My friends from the pond, handy guys. I will ask them, come see me tomorrow.";
"ObtainBoberStage9Dialog1"                 = "I told you to ask someone else, do we all look the same to you?";
"ObtainBoberStage9Dialog2"                 = "Well, do I look like someone who can control the wind?";
"ObtainBoberStage10Answer0"                = "Well, have you heard from your friends?";
"ObtainBoberStage10Dialog0"                = "They said they would do everything in the best possible way, wait a little longer.";
"ObtainBoberStage11Dialog0"                = "Yes! Look what they just sent us - a beautiful, reliable basket for storing eggs (with a lid). And along with the basket they sent a Bober egg - lucky!";
"ObtainBoberStage11Answer0"                = "Truly a stroke of luck! I will have to try and hatch one or two.";
"ObtainFractalStage1Answer0"               = "I see you have been thinking about something a lot lately, is everything okay?";
"ObtainFractalStage1Dialog0"               = "Yes, everything is fine, I am thinking about one interesting task and want to test it in practice, but I have paws. Will you help me?";
"ObtainFractalStage1Dialog1"               = "Thank you! Then take this two-meter stick and go measure the length of the shoreline of our pond. I am very interested in how much you measure.";
"ObtainFractalStage1Answer1"               = "It will take me one day, I will report the results tomorrow.";
"ObtainFractalStage3Answer0"               = "Hi, I measured the length of the coast - it was 4.76 kilometers, what is next?";
"ObtainFractalStage3Dialog0"               = "Very good, very good. Let us write it down - 4.76 kilometers. Now take this smaller ruler and do the same.";
"ObtainFractalStage3Answer1"               = "Okay, I will be back tomorrow with the results.";
"ObtainFractalStage5Answer0"               = "So, the survey is complete and some kind of devilry is going on there. This time the length of the coast was 5.12 kilometers. How so?";
"ObtainFractalStage5Dialog0"               = "That, my dear, is the paradox of the coastline. If you want to know more about it, ask the bobers, they are good not only at carpentry, but also at mathematics.";
"ObtainFractalStage5Answer1"               = "That is what I will do.";
"ObtainFractalStage6Answer0"               = "Hi, frogus said you could explain the coastline paradox to me.";
"ObtainFractalStage6Dialog0"               = "Aaaah, paradoks linii brzegowej? Wiemy, wiemy. Mam o tym bardzo ciekawą książkę. Przeczytaj ją, jest w niej mnóstwo ciekawych rzeczy.";
"ObtainFractalStage6Answer1"               = "Thank you very much, I think I will master it overnight.";
"MeditationStage1Answer0"                  = "Hey, my head is been buzzing with all sorts of thoughts lately. How do you always stay so rested?";
"MeditationStage1Dialog0"                  = "Ah, well, we Doguses have been learning meditation since childhood. Do you want me to teach you?";
"MeditationStage1Dialog1"                  = "To achieve enlightenment, do this:\n1. Get a Frogus - they know everything there is to know about meditation.\n2. As soon as it hatches, start practicing with it right away.\n3. Practice meditating with it every day.\n4. If you miss even one day, start over.\n5. Finishing 10 exercises will allow you to achieve enlightenment.";
"MeditationStage1Answer1"                  = "It sounds confusing, but I will try.";
"MeditationStage2Answer0"                  = "Hi, dogus said you can teach me meditation.";
"MeditationStage2Dialog0"                  = "Great, you have come to the right place. Let us start with something simple – breathing exercises. Repeat after me.";
"MeditationStage2Dialog1"                  = "Sorry, but you are a bit late, you need to find a younger Frogus.";
"MeditationStage2Dialog2"                  = "[Half an hour later] Well, that is great, come tomorrow, we will continue training.";
"MeditationStage3Answer0"                  = "Hi, I came to continue our training.";
"MeditationStage3Dialog0"                  = "You came too early, not even a day has passed since our last training, rest for now.";
"MeditationStage3Dialog1"                  = "Excellent! I see you are rested and ready to continue. Exercise for today is";
"MeditationStage3Dialog2"                  = "Unfortunately, you are more than two days late. That is not how things work. We will have to start all over again.";
"MeditationStage3Answer1"                  = "Oh, oh, what can you do...";
"MeditationStage3Dialog4"                  = "I have nothing more to teach you, child, you already know everything you need to know. From now on, you can free yourself from the thoughts that bother you at will. Congratulations!";
"MeditationStage3Answer2"                  = "Thank you for spending time with me! I have learned a lot.";
"ObtainDragonStage1Answer0"                = "Hi, I have heard some disturbing rumors about the kingdom, do you know what they are all about?";
"ObtainDragonStage1Dialog0"                = "The king was looking for you... but I was tasked with speaking. Time is running out, listen carefully. Last night, the necromancer Valherris infiltrated the royal preserve and stole what should have been guarded for centuries — a dragon egg. The necromancer intends to perform a ritual that will transform the dragon hatchling into a soulless creature. If he succeeds, the world awaits times far more terrible than any war. We have five days, no more.";
"ObtainDragonStage1Answer1"                = "And what do you want from me?";
"ObtainDragonStage1Dialog1"                = "You must assemble a party. Going there alone is certain death. But with the right pets… you have a chance.\n\nListen — you need four:\n- Dogus the warrior, whose strength is like a hammer on an anvil, and whose courage is stronger than steel. He will lead you through any enemy ranks.\n- Catus the mage — Well… that is me. And believe me, without my magic and knowledge of ancient runic paths, you will not get halfway.\n- Frogus the bard — his voice can calm the storm and dispel illusions. You need him not only as a musician — he knows paths hidden from maps.\n- Bober the blacksmith — he is a man of few words, but his hands can repair, destroy, or smelt almost anything. And without him, you will perish in the Ash Caves.";
"ObtainDragonStage1Answer2"                = "Four different pets, yep, I get it.";
"ObtainDragonStage1Dialog2"                = "Return to me when you have gathered them all. Go. Time is our enemy. Find them. Gather a squad. And return the egg... before the world turns to ashes.";
"ObtainDragonStage1Answer3"                = "We will definitely cope!";
"ObtainDragonStage2Answer0"                = "I want you to join our team to save the dragon egg.";
"ObtainDragonStage2Dialog0"                = "Are you absolutely sure about this?";
"ObtainDragonStage2Answer1"                = "Yes, I am sure you are the one we need!";
"ObtainDragonStage2Answer2"                = "Wait, I need to think some more.";
"ObtainDragonStage2Dialog1"                = "Okay, I will go collect everything I need.";
"ObtainDragonStage2Answer3"                = "When you are ready, come to Catus mage, we will meet at his place.";
"ObtainDragonStage2Dialog2"                = "Jestem zaszczycony takim zaufaniem! I will speak in a common language, it will be easier. Are you absolutely sure that I am the one you need?";
"ObtainDragonStage2Answer4"                = "Everyone is assembled, we are ready to move out.";
"ObtainDragonStage2Dialog3"                = "Very well, our first goal is to reach the Misty Gorge. The journey there will take about a day, so do not waste your energy, let us get going!";
"ObtainDragonStage2Answer5"                = "Adventures await!";
"ObtainDragonStage3Answer0"                = "Haven’t we reached the Misty Gorge yet?";
"ObtainDragonStage3Dialog0"                = "Not yet, be patient.";
"ObtainDragonStage4Answer0"                = "We’ve finally arrived, tell us what’s going on here.";
"ObtainDragonStage4Dialog0"                = "We stand at the entrance to a gorge, shrouded in a thick silvery fog. Through it, distant whispers, footsteps, and strange laughter can be heard. The figures in the fog seem to be either human or monsters. I raise my staff, the crystal shimmers with an uncertain light.";
"ObtainDragonStage4Dialog1"                = "Be careful. This is no ordinary fog. It’s saturated with the illusions of the ancient spirits of the gorge. It will distort distances, show false paths, make you see things that aren’t there... or things you’d rather not see at all. I sense that without the right approach, we could wander here for hours — or fall into traps.";
"ObtainDragonStage4Dialog2"                = "Talk to everyone in the group. We all have our own ideas on how to best get through this place. You’ll have to choose the method that seems most suitable. When you’re ready, let me know your decision.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Answer0"                = "How do you propose to get through the Misty Gorge?";
"ObtainDragonStage5Dialog0"                = "I can dispel some of the spell. Not completely, but enough to reveal the true contours of the path. This is the safest path.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Dialog1"                = "To hell with illusions! It’s all smoke and terror. I’ll lead the way, cutting a path with my sword. If there are phantoms, I’ll chop off their heads. If there are traps, I’ll withstand the blow. We’ll get to the end if we simply move forward, not letting the fog take over our minds.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Dialog2"                = "The gorge sings. Do you hear it? These voices respond to the melody. If I find the right rhythm, I can keep us sane and prevent illusions from penetrating our hearts. We will follow my song — it will become the thread that will lead us out of this nightmare.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Dialog3"                = "Illusions? Hm. We’re not afraid of them if we leave our mark. Look: if I drive iron pegs into the ground every twenty steps, we won’t get lost. And illusions... illusions don’t care where the iron is. The work is time-consuming, but reliable.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Answer1"                = "I have heard all the options and am ready to decide what we will do.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Dialog4"                = "Okay, so what did you decide?";
"ObtainDragonStage5Answer2"                = "I agree with Catus’s proposal.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Answer3"                = "I like Dogus’s idea";
"ObtainDragonStage5Answer4"                = "Frogus’s solution seems right.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Answer5"                = "I have confidence in Bober’s approach.";
"ObtainDragonStage5Answer6"                = "Actually, let me think a bit more...";
"ObtainDragonStage5Dialog5"                = "Okay, we trust your judgment. We’ll prepare and act according to the chosen plan. If we try, we’ll be done in an hour. Forward!";
"ObtainDragonStage7Answer0"                = "How did we do?";
"ObtainDragonStage7Dialog0"                = "We passed through the fog quickly and safely. At one point, I almost lost my concentration and one of the illusions almost distorted me, but I managed to pull through and led the group under a magical shield. We’re ready to continue our journey, our next destination is the Forest of Singing Winds, a journey that will take a day. Let’s go!";
"ObtainDragonStage7Dialog1"                = "As expected, we quickly crossed the gorge. Dogus truly demonstrated his mastery of the sword, though it wasn’t particularly effective. One of the lurking illusions distorted half my face, but I noticed it in time and cast a spell to banish it. We’re ready to continue our journey, our next destination is the Forest of Singing Winds, a journey that will take a day. Let’s go!";
"ObtainDragonStage7Dialog2"                = "I didn’t think Frogus’s plan would work, and I was surprised when the ghosts actually began to react to the rhythm of his melody. Not everyone reacted the same way, though — one of the lurking illusions distorted half my face, but I noticed it in time and cast a spell to banish it. We’re ready to continue our journey, our next destination is the Forest of Singing Winds, a journey that will take one day. Let’s go!";
"ObtainDragonStage7Dialog3"                = "The Bober’s plan was indeed sound, albeit very slow. We fiddled around for so long that even the ghosts seemed to tire of it all and lost interest. I, too, soon lost interest, and in vain – one of the lurking illusions (which clearly hadn’t lost interest in us) distorted half my face, but I noticed it in time and banished it with a spell. We’re ready to continue on our way, our next destination is the Forest of Singing Winds, a day’s journey away. Onward!";
"ObtainDragonStage8Answer0"                = "Haven’t we reached the Forest of Singing Winds yet?";
"ObtainDragonStage9Answer0"                = "We’ve finally arrived, tell us what’s going on here.";
"ObtainDragonStage9Dialog0"                = "We enter an ancient forest. The leaves tremble, though there’s barely a breath of wind. The air is filled with quiet yet eerie melodies — as if someone is singing from everywhere and nowhere at once. The voices grow louder, and the mood shifts strangely: now sudden joy, now melancholy, now a desire to stop and listen.";
"ObtainDragonStage9Dialog1"                = "Wait... this is the Forest of Singing Winds. The ancient dryads cast a spell here to repel travelers. These voices affect the mind: they can lull you to sleep, lull you into oblivion, remind you of your most painful memories... We must pass quickly and resist their spell. Otherwise, they will lead us into the thicket, from which no one returns.";
"ObtainDragonStage9Dialog2"                = "As before, talk to everyone in the group. We all have our own ideas on how to best get through this place. You’ll have to choose the method that seems most suitable. When you’re ready, let me know your decision.";
"ObtainDragonStage10Answer0"               = "How do you propose to get through the Forest of Singing Winds?";
"ObtainDragonStage10Answer1"               = "I have heard all the options and am ready to decide what we will do.";
"ObtainDragonStage10Dialog0"               = "I can create a sound barrier, cutting off the dryads’ voices from our senses. A sphere of silence around us will allow us to pass more quickly. But it will require concentration... and if I weaken even for a moment, the spell might break through.";
"ObtainDragonStage10Dialog1"               = "Spells, voices, songs… it’s all nonsense. If we just stick together and walk straight ahead, ignoring the voices, they won’t do anything to us. We plug our ears and move on. What could be so difficult?";
"ObtainDragonStage10Dialog2"               = "Allow me. These melodies are no threat if you know how to respond. I can harmonize with the forest, align its voice with our steps. Then the dryads won’t touch us. I can’t promise the path will be easy... but we’ll remain sane.";
"ObtainDragonStage10Dialog3"               = "Songs, whispers… they’re all empty sounds. If we create our own noise — loud, constant, rhythmic — the enemy’s melodies will lose their power. I can pound my hammer on my shield, setting the tempo. It will be unpleasant for everyone, but we will drown out their music.";
"ObtainDragonStage12Answer0"               = "How did we do this time?";
"ObtainDragonStage12Dialog0"               = "We walked slowly, adjusting to the rhythm of the forest. Frogus certainly knew his stuff — his melody harmonized so well with the forest’s song that, by the end, we heard the dryads’ pleas — they begged us to leave Frogus with them — they liked him so much. It’s a good thing we’d already passed the forest by this time. We are ready to move on, to the Stone Pass, the journey there would take a day. Onward!";
"ObtainDragonStage12Dialog1"               = "My sound barrier worked, and we truly walked in complete silence. However, towards the end, Frogus admitted that his perfect pitch had indeed picked up the dryads’ melodies — they were asking him to stay with them. Now he’s acting out of sorts and muttering occasionally. Don’t worry, he’ll be fine. We’re ready to move on to Stone Pass, it’ll only take a day. Let’s go!";
"ObtainDragonStage12Dialog2"               = "Dogus’s plan was as simple as he was — and it worked! I didn’t expect it, I didn’t expect it. However, in the end, Frogus admitted that his perfect pitch had indeed caught the dryads’ melodies — they were asking him to stay with them. Now he’s acting out of sorts and muttering occasionally. Don’t worry, he’ll be fine. We’re ready to move on to the Stone Pass, it’ll only take a day. Forward!";
"ObtainDragonStage12Dialog3"               = "It seems Beaver has no understanding of music at all. It was miserable for everyone — us, the forest, and the dryads. In the end, Frogus admitted that his perfect pitch had finally caught the dryads’ melodies — they were asking him to stay with them. Now he’s acting out of sorts and muttering occasionally. Don’t worry, he’ll be fine. We’re ready to move on to Stone Pass, it’ll only take a day. Let’s go!";
"ObtainDragonStage13Answer0"               = "Haven’t we reached the Stone Pass yet?";
"ObtainDragonStage14Answer0"               = "We’ve finally arrived, tell us what’s going on here.";
"ObtainDragonStage14Dialog0"               = "At dawn, we ascend a high-mountain trail. The narrow road passes beneath overhanging cliffs. A huge figure appears on the path — a giant of gray stone, as if carved from the mountain itself.";
"ObtainDragonStage14Dialog1"               = "He holds a massive stone club and blocks the way, looking at us with motionless but attentive slit-like eyes.\n\n“Stop. This is my pass,” he says. “No one passes until they prove themselves worthy. Either by strength, or honor, or wisdom. Decide.”";
"ObtainDragonStage14Dialog2"               = "This giant is no simple creature. He is bound by an ancient pact with the mountains: to allow travelers through only after a trial. We must pass, otherwise we’ll have to find a way around… and that would be a waste of an entire day. We need to decide how to convince him. Return to me when you’re ready to make a decision.";
"ObtainDragonStage15Answer0"               = "How do you propose to get through the Stone Pass?";
"ObtainDragonStage15Answer1"               = "I have heard all the options and am ready to decide what we will do.";
"ObtainDragonStage15Dialog0"               = "The giant’s skin is nearly impenetrable, but I have a spell that can blind him momentarily or create the illusion of a detour. We can get through while he’s disoriented. It’s dangerous… but possible.";
"ObtainDragonStage15Dialog1"               = "It’s all perfectly clear. He wants a test, so I’ll give him one. I’ll challenge him to a fair fight, one-on-one. No magic, no tricks. If I can withstand his blow or force him to retreat, he’ll let us pass.";
"ObtainDragonStage15Dialog2"               = "The giant is a great stone soul, let me turn to the ancient songs. I can soothe him, sing him a ballad of peace and freedom of the paths. Giants respect history and music — perhaps he will allow us to pass willingly, without a fight.";
"ObtainDragonStage15Dialog3"               = "The giant is a stone. I am a blacksmith. We speak the same language. Allow me. I will offer to strengthen his club with my iron clamps. Improving the weapon is the best payment. Perhaps he will let us go for the work, without trials.";
"ObtainDragonStage17Answer0"               = "How did we manage to defeat the giant?";
"ObtainDragonStage17Dialog0"               = "Dogus challenged the giant to a fair duel. Despite the difference in height, our brave warrior was head and shoulders above his opponent in terms of weapon mastery. The giant soon conceded defeat and said he would long remember such a skilled warrior. We passed without delay. Well, it’s time to move on to the Ash Caves. Forward!";
"ObtainDragonStage17Dialog1"               = "We barely had time to slip past the giant while he was blinded by my spell. Dogus, a true fighter, was displeased that he wasn’t allowed to challenge the giant to a duel, but the main thing is we slipped past without losses. Well, it’s time to head for the Ash Caves. Forward!";
"ObtainDragonStage17Dialog2"               = "I don’t know whether Frogus made up these legends himself or read them somewhere, but it seems the giant truly enjoyed his stories. At the end, he sat motionless, pensively, gazing into the distance — we realized this was our chance to get through, and we took it. Dogus, however, was dissatisfied with not being allowed to challenge the giant to a duel, but the main thing is we slipped through without losses. Well, time to head for the Ash Caves. Forward!";
"ObtainDragonStage17Dialog3"               = "I had no idea that Bober had brought along a whole arsenal of tools for upgrading and modernizing weapons in the field. The giant was also taken aback by the offer and, after some consideration, agreed. Bober did a splendid job. Dogus was displeased that he wasn’t allowed to challenge the giant to a duel, especially since, he said, giant now had a more powerful weapon than before! However, the main thing is that we got through without losses. Well, time to move on to the Ash Caves. Forward!";
"ObtainDragonStage18Answer0"               = "Haven’t we reached the Ash Caves yet?";
"ObtainDragonStage19Answer0"               = "We’ve finally arrived, tell us what’s going on here.";
"ObtainDragonStage19Dialog0"               = "We descend into dark caves. The walls are covered in runes, and the ground vibrates beneath our feet. Deep below, the clatter of ancient machinery can be heard: the hiss of steam, the rumble of gears, the flashes of lava. Sharp gusts of hot air burst from the side pipes every now and then.";
"ObtainDragonStage19Dialog1"               = "As soon as we take a few steps forward, one of the lattice doors slams behind us, forcing us to move only forward.";
"ObtainDragonStage19Dialog2"               = "Be careful. These caves are the ancient workshops of the Ash Dwarves. Their technology combines mechanics and fiery runes. One mistake and we’ll end up under lava or trapped. But there’s no turning back. We must get through this scorching labyrinth. You know what to do.";
"ObtainDragonStage20Answer0"               = "How do you propose to get through the Ash Caves?";
"ObtainDragonStage20Answer1"               = "I have heard all the options and am ready to decide what we will do.";
"ObtainDragonStage20Dialog0"               = "I have an idea. If we cool the air around us with ice magic, we can slow down some of the mechanisms. This will create a safe passageway. But fire and ice runes conflict… the consequences are unpredictable.";
"ObtainDragonStage20Dialog1"               = "We’re wasting too much time. If we just move quickly, I can get through first and clear the way. Yes, it’s hot in some places, but we can’t stop. We’ll run where the furnaces are active and crawl where it’s too hot.";
"ObtainDragonStage20Dialog2"               = "“The toothed wheels started spinning in my head.\nIn my wet head under the armor-piercing rain.”\n\nListen… these mechanisms work in rhythm. Can you hear it? “Knock-knock-shhhh” — repeating every few seconds. If we move to the rhythm, adjusting to the cycle, we can pass between the stoves and doors without coming into contact with the fire. The main thing is not to lose our rhythm.";
"ObtainDragonStage20Dialog3"               = "This is my element. I know how these machines work. Give me time — I’ll check the pressure in the pipes, jam the dangerous gears, and shut down the unnecessary furnaces. If we follow me and do as I say, we’ll get through without any losses.";
"ObtainDragonStage22Answer0"               = "How did we manage to get through fire, water and copper pipes?";
"ObtainDragonStage22Dialog0"               = "We moved very slowly and carefully, Bober checking any suspicious levers and mechanisms with particular care. A couple of times we stumbled upon some red crystals growing out of the walls, which greatly intrigued Bober, but I hurried him on, reminding him that he was responsible for our safety. Overall, we made it out without any casualties. We’re almost there — it’s a day’s journey from here to the ritual site. Onward!";
"ObtainDragonStage22Dialog1"               = "My plan worked, though it required extreme concentration on my part. Now everyone’s sniffling. In one of the corridors, some red crystals were growing out of the wall, which for some reason caught Bober’s interest. I didn’t have time to dwell on it, he seemed to have grabbed a couple of them, saying he’d study them in more detail later. We’re almost there — it’s a day’s journey from here to the ritual site. Let’s go!";
"ObtainDragonStage22Dialog2"               = "Oh, that Dogus! He always thinks everyone around him is as tough as he is. Frogus and I nearly fell into a crevice trying to keep up with our brave warrior. In one of the corridors, some red crystals were growing out of the wall, which for some reason greatly interested Bober. We didn’t have time to dwell on them, he seemed to have grabbed a couple of them, saying he’d study them in more detail later. We’re almost there — it’s a day’s journey from here to the ritual site. Onward!";
"ObtainDragonStage22Dialog3"               = "Well, that was quite an exercise in rhythm. I had no idea everyone in our group would be such natural dancers. We did lose our rhythm once because of Bober — some red crystals were growing out of the wall in one of the corridors, which for some reason caught his interest. We didn’t have time to dwell on it, but he seemed to have grabbed a couple of them, saying he’d study them in more detail later. We’re almost there — it’s a day’s journey from here to the ritual site. Onward!";
"ObtainDragonStage23Answer0"               = "Haven’t we reached the ritual site yet?";
"ObtainDragonStage24Answer0"               = "We are here, what is going on here?";
"ObtainDragonStage24Dialog0"               = "We climb the shattered steps to the ritual chamber. The doors stand open, and an ominous green light pours from within. The air trembles with eerie whispers. In the center of the chamber stands a dragon’s egg, surrounded by runes. Valherris stands above it — tall, in tattered robes, his eyes as empty as night.";
"ObtainDragonStage24Dialog1"               = "“It’s too late…” the necromancer says. “You’ve come too late. But if you want to die next to this damned egg, I don’t mind.”\nHe waves his hand, and hordes of minions burst from the shadows: skeleton knights, ghosts, shadows, and bone golems.";
"ObtainDragonStage24Dialog2"               = "Valherris, you pathetic fool! Did you think I couldn’t recognize the spell of eternal summoning? You sold your soul in exchange for this final summoning, and your time is numbered! Now we can easily take the egg.";
"ObtainDragonStage24Dialog3"               = "But there’s one problem… We’ll get the egg, but the minions will really be spawning forever. Whatever you say, that damn necromancer was incredibly powerful (now all that’s left of him is a robe on the floor). We don’t have much time, we can’t fight forever. One of us has to escape with the egg, and the others will buy him enough time. Decide, who among us will save the egg?";
"ObtainDragonStage24Answer1"               = "It seems I have no other choice…";
"ObtainDragonStage24Dialog7"               = "But there’s one problem… We’ll get the egg, but the minions will really be spawning forever. Whatever you say, that damn necromancer was incredibly powerful (now all that’s left of him is a robe on the floor). We don’t have much time, we can’t fight forever. I never thought I’d have to resort to the power of the Necronomicon. It’s powerful enough for one of us to hold off the creatures long enough for the others to escape with the egg. Decide which of us will buy the others time?";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer0"               = "You will be the one who saves the egg…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer1"               = "I’m ready to make a choice…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog0"               = "Who did you choose?";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer2"               = "I choose you, Catus…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer3"               = "I choose Dogus…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer4"               = "I choose Frogus…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer5"               = "I choose Bober…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog1"               = "Are you absolutely sure?";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer6"               = "Yes, I am sure.";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer7"               = "Let me think a bit more…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog2"               = "Well, in that case, it’s time to say goodbye. I’m putting Dogus in charge of the team. Talk to him, and I have to go. There’s something I need to sort out…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer8"               = "Goodbye, my friend";
"ObtainDragonStage25Answer9"               = "Catus put you in charge, tell me what happened";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog3"               = "This is how it happened: Catus grabbed his staff, and a blue flame flared on it.\n\n— Necromancy raised these creatures. Magic will stop them. Go away.\n\nDrawing power from the cursed book, he creates a wall of energy that tears the air. The last thing you hear is his quiet voice:\n\n— It was an honor to walk with you.\n\nThe wall explodes with light, burying the mage and the hordes of the dead.";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog4"               = "It’s time to go back, we don’t want his sacrifice to be in vain. The journey home will be easier and quicker, and it will only take one day. Let’s go!";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog6"               = "Dogus places his cloak in your hands — he smiles for the first time in the entire adventure.\n\n— Take the egg. I will hold them back. Go.\n\nTouching the cursed book with his sword, he imbues it with mystical light. Turning, he charges into the ranks of the undead, shouting a battle cry that echoes throughout the hall…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog8"               = "Frogus clutches the lyre to his chest. His eyes are sad, but confident.\n\n— We each have our own song, but the final one is always a solo. Remember me like this... singing.\n\nTouching the cursed book, he raises the lyre and plays a note that cracks the air. The melody cuts through the undead like a blade, and then everything around it. The song fades along with the bard’s life, opening the way for you.";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog10"              = "Bober places his hand on your shoulder and looks at you calmly, as if this were all just another day’s work in the forge.\n\n— Iron bends under the hammer. And fate — under the choices we made. Go. I will bring down the halls behind me.\n\nHe waits until we run across the bridge, then, touching the cursed book, strikes the hammer against a supporting column. The entire temple begins to crumble. The last thing we see is Bober’s silhouette standing amidst the falling stones.";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog13"              = "Dogus places his cloak in your hands — he smiles for the first time in the entire adventure. urning, he charges into the ranks of the undead, shouting a battle cry that echoes throughout the hall…";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog14"              = "Frogus clutches the lyre to his chest. His eyes are sad, but confident. He raises the lyre and plays a note that cracks the air. The melody cuts through the undead like a blade, and then everything around it. The song fades along with the bard’s life, opening the way";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog15"              = "Bober places his hand on your shoulder and looks at you calmly, as if this were all just another day’s work in the forge. He waits until we run across the bridge, then strikes the hammer against a supporting column. The entire temple begins to crumble. The last thing we see is Bober’s silhouette standing amidst the falling stones.";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog16"              = "It’s time to go back, we don’t want their sacrifice to be in vain. The journey home will be easier and quicker, and it will only take one day. Let’s go!";
"ObtainDragonStage25Dialog18"              = "Catus grabs his staff, and a blue flame flares on it. He creates a wall of energy that tears the air. The wall explodes with light, burying the mage and the hordes of the dead.";
"ObtainAlienStage1Answer0"                 = "Hey… Catus, did you see that? Did the sky just explode?";
"ObtainAlienStage1Dialog0"                 = "I saw it. And this, my friend, is not just a firework. This is Betelgeuse.";
"ObtainAlienStage1Answer1"                 = "Betel… who?";
"ObtainAlienStage1Dialog1"                 = "Betelgeuse. A red supergiant. Once a star, it has decided to make a graceful exit — it has gone supernova. Such an event happens once every few thousand years.";
"ObtainAlienStage1Answer2"                 = "Sounds epic.";
"ObtainAlienStage1Dialog2"                 = "Of course. You know what would be really epic? To fly there and see it all with your own eyes.";
"ObtainAlienStage1Answer3"                 = "Hmm… indeed, why not?";
"ObtainAlienStage2Answer0"                 = "Bober, hypothetical question. Can you build… a spaceship?";
"ObtainAlienStage2Dialog0"                 = "Hypothetically? Yes. Practically? Also yes, but with some nuances.";
"ObtainAlienStage2Answer1"                 = "Which ones exactly?";
"ObtainAlienStage2Dialog1"                 = "I need a source of powerful magic. You know, concentrated magic. Without it, the ship won’t get further than the next hill.";
"ObtainAlienStage2Answer2"                 = "Where can I get it?";
"ObtainAlienStage2Dialog2"                 = "At the dragon’s, of course. Where else?";
"ObtainAlienStage3Answer0"                 = "Hi, we need magic. For a flight to a supernova.";
"ObtainAlienStage3Dialog0"                 = "Hmm. A bold wish. And a stupid one. I like it.";
"ObtainAlienStage3Answer1"                 = "So… will you help?";
"ObtainAlienStage3Dialog1"                 = "Take this. This is a clot of pure magic. Don’t drop it. And don’t eat it.";
"ObtainAlienStage3Answer2"                 = "I’ll try.";
"ObtainAlienStage4Answer0"                 = "Hi, I brought a little magic.";
"ObtainAlienStage4Dialog0"                 = "Ooh, that’s some magic! Okay… if it’s here, then the stabilizer, and the magic engine…";
"ObtainAlienStage4Answer1"                 = "I see you are passionate about work, when will the starship be ready?";
"ObtainAlienStage4Dialog1"                 = "Tomorrow, come tomorrow… I wonder if this formula will work…";
"ObtainAlienStage6Answer0"                 = "Hey, how are things with the starship?";
"ObtainAlienStage6Dialog0"                 = "It worked! Everything is according to plan. All systems are operating normally. The magical spaceship is ready. Onward, to the stars!";
"ObtainAlienStage6Answer1"                 = "Onward!";
"ObtainAlienStage8Answer0"                 = "Hello… we’ve been flying for a long time, and Betelgeuse is still far away.";
"ObtainAlienStage8Dialog0"                 = "Well, space is big.";
"ObtainAlienStage8Answer1"                 = "Something’s wrong here…";
"ObtainAlienStage9Answer0"                 = "Hi, do you know why we’re flying so slowly?";
"ObtainAlienStage9Dialog0"                 = "I see your path. It is… ineffective.";
"ObtainAlienStage9Answer1"                 = "In terms of?";
"ObtainAlienStage9Dialog1"                 = "You are flying at normal thrust. Your hyperdrive is turned off.";
"ObtainAlienStage9Answer2"                 = "…what?";
"ObtainAlienStage10Answer0"                = "Bober.";
"ObtainAlienStage10Dialog0"                = "Yes?";
"ObtainAlienStage10Answer1"                = "Did we forget to turn on the hyperdrive?";
"ObtainAlienStage10Dialog2"                = "Yeah, heck… wait a second…";
"ObtainAlienStage10Answer2"                = "Bober, bober…";
"ObtainAlienStage11Answer0"                = "Wow…";
"ObtainAlienStage11Dialog0"                = "Supernova remnants. Gas, light, debris… beautiful. And deadly.";
"ObtainAlienStage11Answer1"                = "Wait. Do you see this?";
"ObtainAlienStage11Dialog1"                = "Signal? Yes. In orbit. Looks like a capsule.";
"ObtainAlienStage11Answer2"                = "Launch the probe. It should return within an hour.";
"ObtainAlienStage13Answer0"                = "The probe has returned with the capsule, it’s time to go home.";
"ObtainAlienStage13Dialog0"                = "Hyperdrive engaged. This time, immediately. The journey home will take one hour.";
"ObtainAlienStage13Answer1"                = "Excellent. I hope no one at home is against alien capsules.";

